#: ../../source/Chapter4.rst:752
# 9d821801fc874a1f9595c50caff1a1a3
msgid "If the outside air temperature is 3°F higher than the minimum value identified above, close the hot air damper. If the outside air temperature is 3°F below the minimum value, open the automatic damper. It is important to set the damper cycle time properly to maintain control stability. A two-minute cycle time is suggested. On large systems with significant air flows, significant damage can occur if the dampers are closed or opened too quickly. Figure 4-15 illustrates pressure rise vs. time. The static pressure can be as high as 13 in. H2O, which is high enough to damage the ductwork."
msgstr ""

